Fifa Dataset Preprocessing¶

The data is extracted from sofifa.com which was found on kaggle.com¶

https://www.kaggle.com/datasets/yagunnersya/fifa-21-messy-raw-dataset-for-cleaning-exploring¶

The given Dataset had the following conditions for Preprocessing¶

1.Convert the height and weight columns to numerical forms¶
2.Remove the unnecessary newline characters from all columns that have them.¶
3.'Value', 'Wage' and "Release Clause' are string columns. Convert them to numbers. For eg, "M" in value column is Million, so multiply the row values by 1,000,000, etc.¶
4.Some columns have 'star' characters. Strip those columns of these stars and make the columns numerical¶
5.Which players are highly valuable but still underpaid (on low wages)? (hint: scatter plot between wage and value)¶

Though the above conditions were met , there were still dirty and null values which had to be dealt with¶

The following workbook contains the Preprocessing of the Data¶

12. Converting the values in to integer type and dealing with values which has 'K' that represent thousand'th values¶

In [179]:
def HitConverter(value):
    if isinstance(value,str) and "K" in value:
        if "." in value:
            value_without_decimal = value.replace('.', '')  
            return value_without_decimal.replace('K', '00')
        else:
            return value.replace('K', '000')
    return value
